Anybody who uses windows, MacOS, iOS, Android, etc.. Most people have likely not thoroughly gone through all of their device settings to disable these settings, on top of that, these operating systems make it quite difficult for you to fully be private, as they used telemetry for their own data and tracking. This includes the myriad of apps that you end up downloading over the use of the phone throughout its lifespan. 

Can it be done? Absolutely. Is it feasible or doable for the average human being? No, absolutely not. Anything less than yes is an unacceptable answer anyways. But this is just my opinion, I've already resigned myself to the fact my data is out there, while that data is totally limited, putting effort into ensuring that all of my data has been removed from the internet, it's just not worth my time/effort.
